snippet.textDisplay:
Would you consider making a video about panic buying? If production of basic goods is maintained and consumption stays unchanged (i.e. people are not eating or pooping more than normal) then there is no need to “stock up” on basic items. But if everyone “stocks up” and production remains unchanged, then it APPEARS as though there are shortages of things, which leads to more panic-buying, and the cycle repeats. And if production ramps up to meet the temporary demand, there will be a glut of un-needed items when the panic-buying ends.

From a class I took once, I understand this happened with gasoline during the oil crisis of 1973. Anyway, just thought given your knack for explaining things and your huge following, a message from you might actually make a real difference. Thanks for your great content!
